stylometry: Safety Stock is the inventory that is carried in excess just in case it is needed if demand is higher than expected.  Obviously it is very helpful to have a set amount of safety stock in your hands but you dont want to get too much safety stock or excess inventory with holding costs start to take over.  Lets say for instance we are talking about footballs in stock during the football season at Dick's SPorting goods.  The safety stock ordered is going to be a littler higher in amount than during the baseball season because demand for footballs is not as high in the spring as it is in the late summer and fall.  If they have to much safety stock in footballs during the fall this will stay on the shelves in the back and cost the company money.  As a company they have to determine how much safety stock they are going to carry and try to balance it based on the expected demand.
